ygData.subject: Re: Lvl 6... Where to go, where to go
ygData.msgSnippet: ... You can take a quick trip over to East commons.  Finding a group should be easy, and the hunting, plentiful.  The ooc attitude is a bit immature there
ygData.messageBody:
Nat Russo wrote:

> From: "Nat Russo" <nrusso@...>
>
> Hi folks,
>
> Just made it to lvl 6. I am presently in North Qeynos and wondering where a
> lvl 6 wiz should go for good hunting. Any advice as to what I should do at
> this level?
>
> Thanks in advance,
> Olatan

You can take a quick trip over to East commons. Finding a group should be
easy, and the hunting, plentiful. The ooc attitude is a bit immature there
though. Single orcs in N. Ro are also possible. You can also do the entance
to many dungeons. ie Guk, Blackburrow, and old Paw (Don't know if its
upgraded yet). Level 8 is when your horizons really expand. Most zones offer
something to hunt at this level..
